South African Bonds Pare Retreat as Interest Rate Left at 5.5%

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-09-22T13:24:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/south-african-bonds-pare-retreat-as-interest-rate-left-at-5-5-.html
South African bonds pared an
earlier retreat after the central bank’s monetary policy
committee left its benchmark rate unchanged at 5.5 percent.  The government’s 6.75 percent bonds due 2021 yielded 8.228
percent at 3:20 p.m. in Johannesburg compared with 8.263 before
the decision was announced. The 13.5 percent notes due 2015
yielded 7 percent compared with 7.03 percent before the
announcement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  